sec.p:
Risk of future deterioration in children with RTIs can now be estimated with reasonable accuracy, using the validated STARWAVe clinical prediction rule (CPR):4
Short illness duration (≤3 days);
Temperature (≥37.8 °C);
Age (<2 years);
Recession;
Wheeze;
Asthma; and
Vomiting.

Methodological rigor was the guiding principle of this study, which improved on a previous one14 by:
basing patient vignettes on real patients;
varying all seven STARWAVe factors systematically;
testing the effects of two new risk-elicitation methods;
ensuring a comprehensive and clinically plausible set of options for patient management; and
testing the effect of a non-clinical factor (parental concern).
